  • Universal Travel Adapter: the adapter comes in a small compact size with 5 USB ports to power all your devices. Includes 4 USB A and 1 Type C smart charging port. Great convenience as you charge up to 6 devices at the same time in just one outlet!
  • Worldwide usage: travel to over 160 countries of the most traveled nations. The power plug adapter is also great for all European outlets. This international travel adapter works in the US, UK, EU, Europe, Canada, Germany, France, Italy, Spain, Australia, Asia, Israel, Africa, and many others.
  • Supports most of your travel gear and it is compatible with devices such as: travel hair dryer, shaver, curling iron, digital camera, tablet, bluetooth speakers, headphones and much more. (Note: This is not a voltage converter, only compatible for dual voltage 100V to 250V wide voltage device)
  • Intelligent safety system: effectively guards from overcharge and short circuit. Comes with one sparefuse inside the adapter. Rated voltage 100-240V, 50/60hz, Max 880W at110V & 1840W at 230V, USB Total output: 5V, 5600mA, Max,Type C output 5V, 3000mA.
  • Compact and Portable Design - Perfect for travelers, whether for business or leisure. This worldwide adapter features a compact travel-friendly size and includes a convenient case. With no surge protection or cords, it is fully cruise ship approved. Please Note that the Type C port is limited to 15W and cannot be used to charge laptops.
  • Satisfaction service -30 days money-back and if there's anything wrong with the adapter, write us and we will fix the problem for free or send you a new replacement (2-Year Warranty). We are an American business and we will reply to you within 24 hours offer great support.

Product description

Worldwide International Travel Adapter

Type C - All of Europe

Compatible in: Brazil, France, Germany, Greece, Italy, Norway, Netherlands, Poland, Portugal, Russia, Spain, Sweden, Korea, Switzerland, Turkey, etc.

Type G - UK, Ireland, Dubai

Compatible in: Dubai, England, Hong Kong, Ireland, Kenya, Macau, Malta, Malaysia, Nigeria, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Scotland, Singapore, Sri Lanka, etc.

Type I - AUS, NZ, China

Compatible in: Argentina, Australia, China, El Salvador, Fiji, Guatemala, Nauru, New Zealand, Panama, Papua New Guinea, Samoa, Tonga, Vanuatu, etc.

Type A - USA, Japan, Canada

Compatible in: Bahamas, Canada, Colombia, Cuba, Ecuador, Haiti, Jamaica, Laos, Mexico, Nicaragua, Panama, Peru, Philippines, Taiwan, Venezuela, etc.

  • Can a hair dryer be used with the adapter?

    Your choice of hair dryer will determine this. In summary, only hair dryers with a power rating of less than 1600W and a label that specifies "100-240V, 50/60Hz" can be used in nations having a 220-240V power supply, like Europe.

  • What should I do if the adapter's AC outlet stops functioning?

    The cause of this is probably a blown fuse. Replace the fuse by prying open the "SPARE & FUSE"-labeled box at the back of the adapter. Please email Proglobe for more help if it still doesn't function.

  • Which nations are compatible with this adapter? Does it work in South Africa?

    It functions in more than 160 nations and territories, including Japan, South Korea, Thailand, the Chinese mainland, France, Germany, Italy, and Spain. In South Africa and India (with a Type D/M socket), it DOES NOT WORK. Write us for more details.

  • What are my options for buying more fuses?

    To buy more fuses, look for "8A Replacement Fuse" on Amazon. Please make sure that the fuses you choose are 8A and correct size, as fuses with improper specs might not work with the item.

  • Can you charge a laptop in the Type C port?

    No. The type C port is 15W and not made for charging laptops.

    Exactly what every traveler needs!

    Color: Blue
    Just returned from a trip to/from the Philippines. This little do-dad worked like a charm. The locations we stayed at had combinations of European, US (2-prong) and UK style plugs. So, we actually used all three prong types within the head- how cool was that! We... See more
    Just returned from a trip to/from the Philippines. This little do-dad worked like a charm. The locations we stayed at had combinations of European, US (2-prong) and UK style plugs. So, we actually used all three prong types within the head- how cool was that! We primarily used this to charge all of our electronics that we brought via the USB connections: multiple cell phones, battery pack, tablets and hand-held fans. We did not use the plug at the top. Bottom line: This little do-dad replaced several plug heads which we didn't have to pack, saving us a bit of space for more "stuff".

    While this is NOT a con- it is something to be aware of in your travels. This does NOT convert power from 240 - 120. This is an adapter, so make sure whatever you plug into the primary plug, it can handle not only the voltage passing through the plug, but the frequency. Most of the world operates at 50Hz, while the US operates at 60Hz. The USB plugs all output 5VDC, so nothing to worry about with them.

    Do I recommend: Absolutely.
